description: We are pleased to offer this 1966 Mustang Custom.  This beautiful grey Mustang with the black racing stripes was restored 2 years ago with several new parts, including all new body panels, new bumpers, new floor pans and new grill.  Only the hood and right rear quarter panel are original.  It has been outfitted with a 289 V8 engine that was completely rebuilt in 2011 with new exhaust, new headers, new gas tank and gas lines.  The Automatic transmission was rebuilt in 2015.   The Air Conditioning was installed a few months ago. The car also has all new wiring including the engine harness, dash harness and taillight harness.   It has a new front and rear windshield.  It has front power disc brakes.   A new AM/FM radio was installed recently.  The interior looks great with new seats, seat belts, carpet, headliner, new gauges, new console and door panels.  The car has a custom stance since it has a 1 drop with new shocks and coils.  This is a great price for a very nice Mustang. We have many receipts from the restoration.  This car is ready to go cruising!  We can arrange shipping to anywhere in the US.   Please contact Savannah Classic Cars office at 912-235-2347 (no texts).
title: 1966 Ford Mustang

description: 1966 Ford Fairlane 289 2 Barrel with Power steering, power brakes, A/C factory. Only has a documented 40761 true miles. The came out of Virginia two owner car. The original owner was handicap and had hand controls to operate the gas and brakes, the brake pedal does not show any wear and the gas pedal has a screw hole. The car was repainted on the outside but care was taken to not over spray the original door jams, bottom of hood and bottom of truck lid and inside the trunk, all of those areas have the original paint. Paint is Tahoe Turquoise U code and the interior is 47 is Aqua. All of the interior is original, dash pad, steering wheel, door panels even the head liner is original. The instrument cluster is original and the chrome plating is original and looks new. It has the factory AM radio and it works. The carpet is original as are the scuff plates, front seat cover has wear on it and the beading has come loose on driver side. It has a original set of Ford optional head rests that where install at dealer, all ash trays were never used and even the lighter looks new. The rear package tray is original. The trunk has the original jack, spare tire and it has the original trunk mat. The car came with the steel wheels paint the color of car and had the dog pan hub caps which goes with the car and they look great! I like the style steel wheels on it and the radial tires they make for a great ride. The engine is original and only has 40K miles on it, runs great had new plugs, plug wires, and coil replaced, I am changing the coil to the correct yellow top and the correct Autolite plug wires. It still has the original starter solenoid with the correct part number and even the A/C compressor switch is correct, Also going to Change out the Battery cables to the correct ones. I have pictures of them in the trunk. Power steering works great and the same for the transmission. The exhaust was changed from a single to duals and sounds great! New rear leaf springs were installed to get the correct ride height with new shackles. This is a mostly original car that was well taken care of and the mileage is low because some years it wasnt driven but a few hundred miles. The under side was under coated at dealer or factory, I have not seen any rust or rust repair. the body is straight and doors close like new. I know it is hard to believe how nice this Fairlane is, but it is one that truly only comes around once in a life time.
title: 1966 Ford Fairlane
